In the global hemp seed market, the segmentation by product type plays a crucial role in understanding consumer preferences and market dynamics. Whole hemp seeds, hulled hemp seeds, hemp seed oil, and hemp protein powder are key product types driving market growth. Whole hemp seeds are favored for their nutritional content, while hulled hemp seeds appeal to consumers looking for a convenient and versatile option. Hemp seed oil and hemp protein powder cater to specific applications such as cooking, skincare, and plant-based protein supplements, indicating a diverse range of offerings to meet varying consumer needs.

